{
  "stem": "10835.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our first son was born April 10-- beg your pardon, April 9.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I get confused, my husband was born April 10-- April 9, 1947.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the meantime, we were able to communicate with our relatives in the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Funny thing, I remember the address of one  of my aunts.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it's stayed in my memory all through these years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Somehow I-- I made sure that it became ingrained in my memory, so I could, if we survive, that we should get be able to get in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And 1947 when my son was born, they sent us packages and things like that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then we already-- we were able to apply for immigration to the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Our family sent us papers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But when my son was three months old, we left Deggendorf.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were-- we were gathered with a lot of other people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was such a temporary camp where we went through the process of being examined by doctors and-- and-- for immigration, American doctors.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had to undergo extensive medical examinations.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In fact, even my three month old baby was examined.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we weren't-- we had to wait for a visa.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we came here under the DP camp, under the Displaced Persons Act that President Truman initiated.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so we, between the time that we were able to-- to go, we stayed with somebody, a cousin of ours in-- in one of the small towns in Germany.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then, in November of 1947, we were given the departure date.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had to gather in one place in Munich.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from there, we went to Bremerhaven.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there we were loaded on a ship called Ernie Pyle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have a picture of the ship.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
